<b>Search/Retrieve Web service</b> (<b>SRW</b>) is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../483/93483.xml">
web service</link> for <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../149/19386149.xml">
search</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
retrieval</link>.  SRW provides a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../215/29215.xml">
SOAP</link> interface to queries, to augment the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../277/32277.xml">
URL</link> interface provided by its companion protocol <artifact wordnetid="100021939" confidence="0.8">
<instrumentality wordnetid="103575240" confidence="0.8">
<engine wordnetid="103287733" confidence="0.8">
<motor wordnetid="103789946" confidence="0.8">
<device wordnetid="103183080" confidence="0.8">
<machine wordnetid="103699975" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../350/8465350.xml">
Search/Retrieve via URL</link></machine>
</device>
</motor>
</engine>
</instrumentality>
</artifact>
 (SRU).  Queries in SRU and SRW are expressed using the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../320/9672320.xml">
Common Query Language</link> (CQL).<p>

Standards for SRW, SRU, and CQL are promulgated by the United States <library wordnetid="103660909" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../081/18944081.xml">
Library of Congress</link></library>
.</p>

